Based on the search results, here's what I found about Adobe UXP range slider issues and fixes:

## Key Findings

### Event Listener Limitations
The standard range slider `input type="range"` will only take `input` and `change` as event listeners and does not respond to other events like mousedown, mouseup etc.

### Recommended Approach
You can use native elements like the range slider, but Spectrum components are recommended. The native range slider works but isn't as visually appealing, whereas the Spectrum slider is "nicer." You should use Spectrum components where possible because this will keep the look consistent.

### Known Issues to Be Aware Of
Until issues are fixed in UXP, you may need to add logic to prevent infinite loops or use a native widget instead.(no content)There are known issues that are important to understand "because many things won't work as you would expect them to do."

### Working with Multiple Sliders
For multiple sliders where you need values to persist, you can implement multiple event listeners. Example: `document.getElementById("blendifdarkSlider").addEventListener("mouseup", evt => {...`

### Debugging Tips
If your plugin fails to run due to a JavaScript error, usually that error will show up in the debugger console. The error message may be buried in a cryptic stack trace, but it will be there with the offending JavaScript line number displayed at the top right of the trace.

### Key Fix
For range sliders in UXP, **use `input` or `change` events** instead of mouse events:

```javascript
// This works:
slider.addEventListener("input", (e) => {
    console.log(e.target.value);
});

// Or:
slider.addEventListener("change", (e) => {
    console.log(e.target.value);
});

// This does NOT work:
slider.addEventListener("mouseup", (e) => {...}); // Not supported
```

You can find more details in the [Adobe UXP Known Issues documentation](https://developer.adobe.com/photoshop/uxp/2022/uxp-api/known-issues/) and the [Adobe Creative Cloud Developer Forums](https://forums.creativeclouddeveloper.com/).


