# Range Input CSS Styling Guide

## Base CSS Styles

The foundational styles reset range inputs across browsers:

```css
input[type=range] {
  -webkit-appearance: none;
  width: 100%;
  background: transparent;
}

input[type=range]:focus {
  outline: none;
}

input[type=range]::-ms-track {
  width: 100%;
  cursor: pointer;
  background: transparent;
  border-color: transparent;
  color: transparent;
}
```

## Thumb Styling

The draggable element uses vendor-specific pseudo-selectors:

```css
input[type=range]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
  -webkit-appearance: none;
  border: 1px solid #000000;
  height: 36px;
  width: 16px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  background: #ffffff;
  cursor: pointer;
  margin-top: -14px;
  box-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #000000;
}

input[type=range]::-moz-range-thumb {
  border: 1px solid #000000;
  height: 36px;
  width: 16px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  background: #ffffff;
  cursor: pointer;
  box-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #000000;
}

input[type=range]::-ms-thumb {
  border: 1px solid #000000;
  height: 36px;
  width: 16px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  background: #ffffff;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

## Track Styling

The background rail requires separate handling per browser:

```css
input[type=range]::-webkit-slider-runnable-track {
  width: 100%;
  height: 8.4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  background: #3071a9;
  border-radius: 1.3px;
  border: 0.2px solid #010101;
  box-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #000000;
}

input[type=range]:focus::-webkit-slider-runnable-track {
  background: #367ebd;
}

input[type=range]::-moz-range-track {
  width: 100%;
  height: 8.4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  background: #3071a9;
  border-radius: 1.3px;
  border: 0.2px solid #010101;
}
```

## IE-Specific Track Sections

Internet Explorer allows separate styling for filled/unfilled portions:

```css
input[type=range]::-ms-fill-lower {
  background: #2a6495;
  border: 0.2px solid #010101;
  border-radius: 2.6px;
  box-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #000000;
}

input[type=range]::-ms-fill-upper {
  background: #3071a9;
  border: 0.2px solid #010101;
  border-radius: 2.6px;
  box-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #000000;
}

input[type=range]:focus::-ms-fill-lower {
  background: #3071a9;
}

input[type=range]:focus::-ms-fill-upper {
  background: #367ebd;
}
```

## Notes

The article emphasizes that "you can't comma-separate these type of selectors" due to browser specifications—each vendor prefix requires its own rule block.

